                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/1403a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-14T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>91. For General Russell.</p>
                <p>Please inform President Borno that the President has nominated Mr. John S. Hord
                    as Financial Adviser to Haiti in place of Mr. <pb facs="0586" n="472"
                        xml:id="pg_472"/> McIlhenny, and request that Hord’s appointment, as in
                    similar cases, be made effective from this date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
